can stimulate M2-polarized macrophages via the paracrine communication [11]. Exosomes mediate the material transfer and information communication between cells, as lipid doublecoated extracellular vesicles containing proteins, nucleic acids and
metabolites [32]. Our study revealed that PDAC-derived exosomal CCT6A functions as matchmaker to efficiently introduce chemokines into TAMs, which leads to increased M2-polarized macrophages.
T. Ma et al.
